The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, July 11: The government is planning to set up five manufacturing investment regions and revise foreign direct investment norms for the manufacturing sector to boost growth. ?We are looking at how, if at all required, the FDI in manufacturing can be further liberalised. There is a scope for it,? commerce and industry minister Kamal Nath said today. The government has received many recommendations on liberalising the FDI norms and they were being studied, he added.

 New Delhi, July 11: The government has collected Rs 43,199 crore from indirect taxes, excluding services tax, during the first quarter of the current fiscal, up 18.5 per cent year-on year.

 Mumbai, July 11: Arvind Mills Ltd today said it would demerge the garments business division of Arvind brands and plans to amalgamate Arvind Fashions with itself.

 Mumbai, July 11: Nationalised banks as a group accounted for 48.4 per cent of the aggregate deposits at Rs 20,93,042 crore in the quarter ended March 31, 2006. The State Bank of India and its associates accounted for 23.4 per cent of this.

 Mumbai, July 11: Tata Power has signed a development agreement with Germany?s Siemens Project Ventures to jointly bid for ultra-mega power projects.




